    <section class="destination-section">
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Bled Castle &amp; Bled Island</h2>
        <p>The town of Bled sits on incredibly scenic Bled Lake, which is the focal point of the attractions here. Next to the town atop a hill high above the lake you'll find the 1,000 year old <strong>Bled Castle</strong>, an incredibly well-preserved structure offering a museum and spectacular views over Lake Bled. You can also enjoy great views of the castle set amongst the lake from the southern coastline of the town of Bled.</p>
        <p>In the middle of Lake Bled is the tiny <strong>Bled Island</strong> where you'll find a stunning old church, cafe, and several other structures along with views of the hills surrounding the lake and views of Bled Castle.</p>
    </section>



    <!-- Bled Lake Viewpoints Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Bled Lake Viewpoints</h2>
        <p>On the western side off the lake are two viewpoints very close to each other, the <strong>Ojstrica Mountain Viewpoint</strong>, which is said to be the most gorgeous view over the lake, and the <strong>Mala Osojnica</strong> hilltop viewpoint, both offering slightly different perspectives. Both are reached by short but steep hiking trails.</p>
        <p>You might alternatively consider taking the cable car up to <strong>Straza Hill</strong> on the southeastern side of the lake which also offers excellent views, and can also be reached by hiking if you like.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- Vintgar Gorge Trail Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Vintgar Gorge Trail</h2>
        <p>A must-see attraction in Bled is the <strong>Vintgar Gorge</strong>, a breathtaking river gorge trail through a lush forested canyon. There is a bus that runs from Bled to the Vintgar Gorge you can take that runs in the summer, however in the calmer seasons you may need to take a taxi or take a bus to the closest villages and walk the last 1 mile (1.6 km) to the entrance of the gorge.</p>
        <p>The total trail length of the gorge is approximately 2 miles (3.2 km) in and back and is definitely worth the effort, however plan to spend a descent amount of time here as it can be quite crowded with long lines due to its popularity.</p>
    </section>




